=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Start from methyl 2-(1,2,3,4-tetrahydroisoquinolin-7-yl)acetate; N-alkylate the THIQ nitrogen with 3-bromopropyl phthalimide (or 3-Boc-aminopropyl halide) to give methyl 2-[2-(3-protected-aminopropyl)-1,2,3,4-tetrahydroisoquinolin-7-yl]acetate. | Step 2: Remove the amine protecting group to obtain the primary amine methyl 2-[2-(3-aminopropyl)-1,2,3,4-tetrahydroisoquinolin-7-yl]acetate. | Step 3: Reductive amination with 4-(trifluoromethoxy)benzaldehyde (NaBH(OAc)3) furnishes the secondary amine methyl 2-[2-(3-((4-(trifluoromethoxy)benzyl)amino)propyl)-1,2,3,4-tetrahydroisoquinolin-7-yl]acetate. | Step 4: Couple this secondary amine with 4-chloro-6-ethylpyrimidine by SNAr to install the heteroaryl group, giving methyl 2-[2-(3-((6-ethylpyrimidin-4-yl)((4-(trifluoromethoxy)benzyl)amino))propyl)-1,2,3,4-tetrahydroisoquinolin-7-yl]acetate. | Step 5: Hydrolyze the methyl ester (LiOH or NaOH, then acid workup) to the acid, affording CCc1cnc(N(CCCN2CCc3ccc(CC(=O)O)cc3C2)Cc2ccc(OC(F)(F)F)cc2)nc1.

